The paper deals with the calibration of Augmented Reality devices in robotic environments, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The use of a 3D depth sensor for calibration involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and the manipulation of 3D point cloud data (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the usability and flexibility of the proposed method, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM).
